cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is about training large-scale implicit generative models using a method of moments algorithm. The paper focuses on using neural networks to define moments and using asymptotic theory to determine which moments are useful. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses image data and achieves high-quality image generation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses optimization and objective functions, which could place it in cs.GR (Graphics).
